( 1. Problem Statement) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter analyses fictitious ad-click traffic to identify events that look) Tj
T*
(more like automated bot activity than legitimate user behaviour. The input is) Tj
T*
(an unlabelled click log, so the task is not to prove fraud event by event. The) Tj
T*
(task is to find defensible anomaly patterns, explain the evidence behind them,) Tj
T*
(and produce a binary submission.tsv prediction where false positives and) Tj
T*
(false negatives are treated as roughly equal in cost.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This run read data/bot-hunter-dataset.tsv and analysed 149,239 click) Tj
T*
(events. Each row contains an event identifier, timestamp, region, browser,) Tj
T*
(operating system, and click URL. The URL query string carries behaviour signals) Tj
T*
(such as clicked domain \(d\), search query \(q\), time to click \(ttc\), and) Tj
T*
(country-like context \(ct\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This report should be read as evidence for review, not as proof of fraud for) Tj
T*
(every individual event. The dataset does not include ground-truth labels, so the) Tj
T*
(system cannot claim measured precision, measured recall, or a calibrated fraud) Tj
T*
(probability.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The submitted output is submission.tsv. It keeps the required binary) Tj
T*
(is_bot decision and adds operational_tier so the same prediction can be) Tj
T*
(used carefully in business workflows.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 2. Methodology And Rationale) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter uses two classifiers because each covers a different risk. The) Tj
T*
(rules classifier catches patterns that are easy to explain and audit, such as) Tj
T*
(repeated query/domain pairs, mechanical timing, and dense bursts. The) Tj
T*
(Extended Isolation Forest model catches unusual combinations across engineered features) Tj
T*
(that) Tj
T*
(fixed rules may miss.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Component | Current choice | Why this choice was made |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Rules classifier | Weighted heuristic rules | Transparent, auditable, and suitable for) Tj
T*
(explaining repeated or mechanical click patterns. |) Tj
T*
(| ML classifier | Extended Isolation Forest model | Works without labels and can detect) Tj
T*
(unusual combinations across engineered features. |) Tj
T*
(| Score blend | 0.58 * heuristic_score + 0.42 * ml_score | Keeps explainable rule) Tj
T*
