T*
( Appendix C: Model Definition) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Extended Isolation Forest is an unsupervised anomaly-detection model. It does) Tj
T*
(not learn from known bot labels. Instead, it asks which events are easier to) Tj
T*
(isolate from the rest of the batch using random feature-space splits.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In plain English, events that look very different from the main population tend) Tj
T*
(to be isolated more quickly and receive higher anomaly scores. This is useful) Tj
T*
(for an unlabelled dataset, but it also means the model detects unusual) Tj
T*
(behaviour rather than confirmed fraud. The model output is strongest when it) Tj
T*
(agrees with transparent rule evidence and weakest when it stands alone without) Tj
T*
(feature-deviation review.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( Appendix D: Thresholds And Decision Logic) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(An event is selected as a bot when either condition is true:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(text) Tj
T*
(combined_score > 0.568053) Tj
T*
(or heuristic_score >= 0.62) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The combined-score threshold is the run-specific 97.5th-percentile cutoff. It) Tj
T*
(keeps the selected volume stable for an unlabelled dataset while letting the ML) Tj
T*
(model influence borderline cases.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The heuristic override protects high-confidence, explainable rule hits. For) Tj
T*
(example, a strongly repeated query/domain pattern with mechanical timing should) Tj
T*
(not be missed only because the anomaly ranking moved after a feature change.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Adaptive heuristic thresholds used in this run:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Rule | Computed threshold | Basis |) Tj
T*
ET
